  "prompt": "What are good gifts for a foreign visitor to bring when they're invited to someone's home in Liechtenstein for the first time?",
  "response": "When visiting someone's home in Liechtenstein for the first time, here are some appropriate gift ideas:\n\n1. High-quality chocolates or sweets from your home country\n2. A nice bottle of wine (preferably from a reputable winery)\n3. Flowers (avoid chrysanthemums, which are associated with funerals)\n4. A small gift or souvenir from your home country\n5. A gourmet food item or specialty from your region\n6. A book about your country or culture (if the hosts speak English)\n\nSome cultural tips:\n- Avoid overly expensive gifts, as this can make hosts uncomfortable\n- Wrap the gift nicely\n- Present the gift with both hands\n- If bringing wine, it's best if it's from a good vineyard\n- Avoid giving anything too personal or intimate\n\nLiechtensteiners appreciate thoughtful, tasteful gifts that show consideration and respect for their hospitality.",
